reasoning.structural: Codes assigned by authorities, not strategic choice. Very constrained.
reasoning.temporal: Some evolution over time (reputation, incidents), but core identity fixed.
reasoning.agency: Limited agency. Engineering/regulation determine outcomes, not names.
reasoning.interpretation: Objective metrics. Incidents are facts, not interpretations. High observability.
reasoning.format: Rigid format (3-letter IATA, 4-letter ICAO codes). Industry conventions.
